INTEL BAYTRAIL I2C Driver

Syntax:
%C [device options] [generic options]

Example:
%C -d0x0F41 -vvv -r0x8086 --u0 --b100000

Device options:
-c  i2c_clock       I2C input clock (Default: 0)
-d  device_id       PCI device ID of the I2C bus (Default: 0xFFFF)
-h  sda_hold_time   I2C SDA hold time in units of i2c_clk period (Default: 0)
-i  device_index    PCI device index (Default: 0)
-I                  Set SCL and Holt registers to Intel Recommended values(Case:00168315)
                    Note: -r value will be ignored and the Hold time will be a constant
                    value when -I option is used (Default: disabled)
-q  irq_number      I2C interrupt number (Default: -1)
-r  vendor_id       PCI vendor ID of the I2C bus (Default: 0x8086)
-v  verbose         I2C verbosity level (Default: 2)

Generic options:
--b bus_speed       Default bus speed (Default: 100000)
--u unit            Unit number (Default: 0)
